OL,6,F"We are of course disappointed with
OL,7,Fthe outcome, however we feel the
OL,8,Freports provide a constructive and
OL,9,Fcomprehensive sense of the areas we
OL,10,Fmust target for improvement to ensure
OL,11,Fwe meet the needs of women and
OL,12,Fbirthing people and their babies in
OL,13,FNorth and East Devon."
OL,15,FShe added: "We are pleased that a
OL,16,Fnumber of strengths have shone through
OL,17,Fand we will build on these as we work
OL,18,Ftogether with our colleagues, patients
OL,19,Fand partners to improve our services.
